.TH "slim_msg_response" 9 "slim_msg_response" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
slim_msg_response \- Deliver Message response received from a device to the framework.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" slim_msg_response
.BI "(struct slim_controller *ctrl "  ","
.BI "u8 *reply "  ","
.BI "u8 tid "  ","
.BI "u8 len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctrl" 12
Controller handle
.IP "reply" 12
Reply received from the device
.IP "tid" 12
Transaction ID received with which framework can associate reply.
.IP "len" 12
Length of the reply
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called by controller to inform framework about the response received.
This helps in making the API asynchronous, and controller-driver doesn't need
to manage 1 more table other than the one managed by framework mapping TID
with buffers
